bug.summary: Problem exporting to onnx with the latest update
bug.description:
Before submitting a bug report, please be aware that your issue must be reproducible with all of the following, otherwise it is non-actionable, and we can not help you:
Current repo: run git fetch && git status -uno to check and git pull to update repo Common dataset: coco.yaml or coco128.yaml Common environment: Colab, Google Cloud, or Docker image. See https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov5#environments
If this is a custom dataset/training question you must include your train*.jpg, test*.jpg and results.png figures, or we can not help you. You can generate these with utils.plot_results(). <denchmark-h:h2>üêõ Bug</denchmark-h>
Onnx export do not work now <denchmark-h:h2>To Reproduce (REQUIRED)</denchmark-h>
run export.py in yolov5 docker Input: <denchmark-code>python models/export.py </denchmark-code>
Output: <denchmark-code>ONNX export failure: Exporting the operator hardswish to ONNX opset version 12 is not supported. Please open a bug to request ONNX export support for the missing operator.
</denchmark-code>
<denchmark-h:h2>Expected behavior</denchmark-h>
Correctly exported onnx file <denchmark-h:h2>Environment</denchmark-h>
Official docker <denchmark-h:h2>Additional context</denchmark-h>
Add any other context about the problem here.
